request.description:
OTP verify karke account create karta hai.

**Response (201)**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Account created successfully",
  "data": {
    "accessToken": "...",   // 15 min validity
    "refreshToken": "...",  // 30 days validity
    "user": { "id": 12, "phone": "...", "role": "passenger", "fullName": "..." }
  }
}
```

**Frontend kya kare**: Tokens secure storage (Keychain / EncryptedSharedPreferences) mein save karo. `accessToken` har request ke `Authorization: Bearer ...` header mein bhejo.

OTP verify karke login complete karta hai.

**Response (200)**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Login successful",
  "data": {
    "accessToken": "...",
    "refreshToken": "...",
    "user": { "id": 12, "role": "passenger", ... }
    // driver role ke liye `kycStatus` bhi milta hai
  }
}
```

💡 Test script automatically tokens ko collection variables mein save kar deti hai — baaki requests turant chal jaayengi.

